88
00:03:27,265 --> 00:03:29,675
It's all useful information,

89
00:03:29,675 --> 00:03:31,910
but a little hard to
wrap your head around.

90
00:03:31,910 --> 00:03:34,570
We want a report
that's easier to read.

91
00:03:34,570 --> 00:03:36,230
Let's say your stakeholders want

92
00:03:36,230 --> 00:03:39,020
a quick look at the
revenue by salesperson.

93
00:03:39,020 --> 00:03:41,540
Using the data, you
could make them a pivot

94
00:03:41,540 --> 00:03:44,815
table with a graph that
shows that information.

95
00:03:44,815 --> 00:03:46,130
A pivot table is

96
00:03:46,130 --> 00:03:47,720
a data summarization tool

97
00:03:47,720 --> 00:03:49,655
that is used in data processing.

98
00:03:49,655 --> 00:03:53,855
Pivot tables are used to
summarize, sort, re-organize,

99
00:03:53,855 --> 00:03:56,135
group, count, total,

100
00:03:56,135 --> 00:03:58,610
or average data
stored in a database.

101
00:03:58,610 --> 00:04:00,830
It allows its users to transform

102
00:04:00,830 --> 00:04:03,905
columns into rows and
rows into columns.

103
00:04:03,905 --> 00:04:06,665
We'll actually learn more
about pivot tables later.

104
00:04:06,665 --> 00:04:08,470
But I'll show you
one really quick.

105
