We'll select the Data menu
and click Pivot table button.

106
00:04:12,545 --> 00:04:14,675
It can pull data from this table.

107
00:04:14,675 --> 00:04:15,890
We can just press

108
00:04:15,890 --> 00:04:18,290
create and it'll pull
up a new worksheet.

109
00:04:18,290 --> 00:04:19,730
Over here, it gives us

110
00:04:19,730 --> 00:04:21,835
the pivot table fields
we can choose from.

111
00:04:21,835 --> 00:04:26,620
Click select, salesperson
and revenue.

112
00:04:26,990 --> 00:04:30,260
Just like that, it
made a chart for us.

113
00:04:30,260 --> 00:04:31,700
At this point, you can

114
00:04:31,700 --> 00:04:33,575
play around with how
the graph looks,

115
00:04:33,575 --> 00:04:36,525
but the information is all there.

116
00:04:36,525 --> 00:04:38,130
Let's move on to dashboards.

117
00:04:38,130 --> 00:04:39,860
If you need a more dynamic way to

118
00:04:39,860 --> 00:04:41,960
share information with
your stakeholders,

119
00:04:41,960 --> 00:04:43,370
dashboards are your friend.

120
